  </oversight_info>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Chronic inguinal neuralgia is one of the most important complications following inguinal
      hernia repair.

      It may even outweigh the benefit of the operation. Intraoperative neurectomy has been
      investigated to reduce the incidence of chronic pain.

      This study evaluates the effects of elective division of the ilioinguinal, iliohypogastric
      and genital branch of the genitofemoral nerves on pain and postoperative sensory symptoms
      after Lichtenstein hernia repair.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
